    "GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation) and CCPA (California Consumer Privacy Act) are data protection and privacy regulations that set guidelines for collecting, processing, and storing personal data.",
    "While GDPR is a European Union regulation, CCPA is specific to the state of California in the United States.",
    "Both regulations are designed to protect individuals' privacy rights and give them greater control over their personal information, including when using AI [58].",
    "The use of DevSecOps methods is needed for the protection of AI systems from potential cyber threats.",
    "Furthermore, the capacity to accommodate a growing user base without compromising precision or consistency is a key factor for successful AI implementation."
